  "text": "The TGF-β pathway, particularly TGF-β2, was downregulated when JMJD6 was overexpressed and induced when JMJD6 was depleted. We validated the inverse relation between JMJD6 and TGF-b2 at both RNA and protein levels in these cellular systems. We extended this observation to clinical samples and observed an inverse correlation between JMJD6 and TGF-b2 in our breast cancer cohorts. Such antagonistic roles of JMJD6 and TGF-β2 have a precedent in eye development. One of the distinctive developmental defects of JMJD6- knockout mice is the thinning of the retinal layer [CITATION_1] . Coincidentally, the knockout of TGF-β2 results in the hyperplasia of the neuroblastic layer of the retina [CITATION_2] . These data suggest that JMJD6 and TGF-β2 may be functionally linked in cell-cycle regulation and in development.",
